CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 27, 1951, page 6, reads: "Collegiate Press Delegates - While attending the Associate Collegiate Press Conference at the William Penn Hotel last week, three of the delegates took time out to visit the Courier. The trio is pictured above with Mrs. Hazel Garland, associate editor of the Courier Magazine Section, discussing an interesting topic. Left to right: Cardinal Williams, editor-in-chief of the Virginia State College; B. F. Dabney, director of public relations, Virginia State College, and George A. Persons, editor-in-chief, Howard University. Hilltop. Washington D.C. - Teenie Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Cardinal Williams, B. F. Dabney, and George A. Persons wearing name tags for ACP (Associated Collegiate Press) conference, standing behind Hazel Garland in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper office
